      56                 :            : // MapEntry is the returned google::protobuf::Message when calling AddMessage of
      57                 :            : // google::protobuf::Reflection. In order to let it work with generated message
      58                 :            : // reflection, its in-memory type is the same as generated message with the same
      59                 :            : // fields. However, in order to decide the in-memory type of key/value, we need
      60                 :            : // to know both their cpp type in generated api and proto type. In
      61                 :            : // implementation, all in-memory types have related wire format functions to
      62                 :            : // support except ArenaStringPtr. Therefore, we need to define another type with
      63                 :            : // supporting wire format functions. Since this type is only used as return type
      64                 :            : // of MapEntry accessors, it's named MapEntry accessor type.
      65                 :            : //
      66                 :            : // cpp type:               the type visible to users in public API.
      67                 :            : // proto type:             WireFormatLite::FieldType of the field.
      68                 :            : // in-memory type:         type of the data member used to stored this field.
      69                 :            : // MapEntry accessor type: type used in MapEntry getters/mutators to access the
      70                 :            : //                         field.
      71                 :            : //
      72                 :            : // cpp type | proto type  | in-memory type | MapEntry accessor type
      73                 :            : // int32      TYPE_INT32    int32            int32
      74                 :            : // int32      TYPE_FIXED32  int32            int32
      75                 :            : // string     TYPE_STRING   ArenaStringPtr   string
      76                 :            : // FooEnum    TYPE_ENUM     int              int
      77                 :            : // FooMessage TYPE_MESSAGE  FooMessage*      FooMessage
      78                 :            : //
      79                 :            : // The in-memory types of primitive types can be inferred from its proto type,
      80                 :            : // while we need to explicitly specify the cpp type if proto type is
      81                 :            : // TYPE_MESSAGE to infer the in-memory type.  Moreover, default_enum_value is
      82                 :            : // used to initialize enum field in proto2.
      83                 :            : template <typename Derived, typename Key, typename Value,
      84                 :            :           WireFormatLite::FieldType kKeyFieldType,
      85                 :            :           WireFormatLite::FieldType kValueFieldType, int default_enum_value>
